<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sojourn2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sojourn,</orth> vb. <emph>(sójourn</emph> and <emph>sojoúrn)</emph> to stay, to dwell for a time: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 171</bibl> <emph>(my heart to her but as guest-wise sojourned; to her</emph> the dat. commodi). <bibl n="shak. jn 1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.206" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 24</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>